---
import ReportLayout from '@/components/ReportLayout.astro';
---

<ReportLayout title="The design system file">

  <section class="guide-intro">
    <p class="guide-eyebrow">For the Myprotein design team</p>
    <h1 class="guide-h1">The design system file</h1>
    <p class="guide-lead">
      The design system file is where our design decisions live. Colours, type styles,
      spacing — all of it is defined here and connected to your working files as a Figma
      library. Using it means your designs are always built on the right foundations, and
      when values change, your files update automatically.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 1 ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Connecting the library</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      The design system is published as a Figma library. To use it in a working file, open the
      assets panel, click the book icon, find the Myprotein design system, and switch it on.
    </p>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Once connected, all the variables — colours, spacing, border radius — are available in
      the right panel whenever you're designing. It's a one-time step per file.
    </p>
    <div class="takeaway">
      <p class="takeaway-label">What to do instead</p>
      <p>
        Before you start a new file, connect the library first. Working without it means
        anything you build will need to be reconnected and corrected later.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 2 ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">What's in it</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Right now the file covers the foundations — colour, typography, spacing, border radius,
      and elevation. Here's what's available:
    </p>

    <div class="spec-list">
      <div class="spec-item">
        <h3 class="spec-title">Colour</h3>
        <p class="spec-desc">
          The full palette organised into Primary, Secondary, Accent, Monochrome, and Platform
          messaging (success, error, attention). Every colour is available as a variable, so
          when you apply a fill you're applying a named colour, not a hex code.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-item">
        <h3 class="spec-title">Typography</h3>
        <p class="spec-desc">
          The full type scale from <code>text-xs</code> through to <code>text-4xl</code>, each
          available in Regular, Medium, and Bold where applicable. Applied as named text styles
          so font size, weight, and line height are all captured in one click.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-item">
        <h3 class="spec-title">Spacing</h3>
        <p class="spec-desc">
          A set of spacing tokens from <code>sp-1</code> (4px) through to <code>sp-16</code>
          (64px), covering everything from tight component gaps to page gutters. Use these for
          padding and gap values in auto-layout rather than typing in numbers manually.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-item">
        <h3 class="spec-title">Border radius</h3>
        <p class="spec-desc">
          A scale from <code>r-xs</code> (4px, for things like tags) through to
          <code>r-full</code> (9999px, for badges and steppers), with named stops for common
          use cases like cards (<code>r-md</code>, 12px) and primary CTAs
          (<code>r-2xl</code>, 32px).
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="spec-item">
        <h3 class="spec-title">Elevation</h3>
        <p class="spec-desc">
          Three shadow levels: <code>shadow-1</code> for tiles and CTAs, <code>shadow-2</code>
          for hover states, <code>shadow-3</code> for modals.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 3 ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">How updates work</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      The token values — colours, spacing, border radius — are stored in a GitHub repository.
      When a change is needed (a colour value is corrected, a new spacing token is added), it
      gets updated in the repo.
    </p>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Any designer on the team can then pull those changes into Figma using the Tokens Studio
      plugin. Once synced, the library updates and those changes flow through automatically to
      any working file that's connected to it.
    </p>
    <div class="takeaway">
      <p class="takeaway-label">What to do instead</p>
      <p>
        You don't need to do anything to receive updates once your file is connected. But if
        you're the one running the sync, let the team know so everyone's aware the library has
        changed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Section 4 ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">What's coming</h2>
    <p class="guide-body">
      Components are being built out and will be added to the library progressively. When
      they're ready they'll appear in the assets panel alongside the variables. In the
      meantime, the foundations are stable and ready to use.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Closing ────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="guide-closing">
    <p>
      If something looks wrong — a colour value that doesn't match the site, a spacing token
      that seems off — don't work around it. Flag it. The whole point of a shared system is
      that fixing it once fixes it everywhere.
    </p>
  </section>

</ReportLayout>

<style>
  .guide-intro { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .guide-eyebrow {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .guide-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 40px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .guide-lead {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .guide-lead:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .guide-section {
    margin-bottom: 44px;
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .section-heading {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .guide-body {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .guide-body:last-of-type { margin-bottom: 16px; }

  .takeaway {
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-mint);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    padding: 14px 18px;
  }
  .takeaway-label {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 800;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.55;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .takeaway p:not(.takeaway-label) {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  .spec-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-top: 20px;
  }
  .spec-item {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    padding: 16px 18px;
  }
  .spec-title {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .spec-desc {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Fira Code', monospace;
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .takeaway code {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);
  }

  .guide-closing {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-top: 56px;
    padding-top: 28px;
    border-top: 2px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
  }
  .guide-closing p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .guide-h1 { font-size: 28px; }
    .section-heading { font-size: 18px; }
  }
</style>
